{
  "name": "Restful Hearth",
  "type": "feat",
  "system": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p>Starting at 6th level, when friends rest near your fire, they feel robust and ready to take on anything. When you finish a short or long rest, select a number of creatures equal to your Wisdom modifier that just finished a short or long rest taken within 30 feet of a fire lit by your create bonfire cantrip. Each creature gains resistance to one damage type of your choice: force, radiant, necrotic, or psychic. The effect lasts until the creature finishes its next short or long rest.</p><p>In addition, when you finish a long rest, every creature of your choice that just finished a long rest taken within 30 feet of a fire lit by your create bonfire cantrip reduces its exhaustion level by 1.</p>",
